{{multiple issues| {{disputed|date=December 2016}} {{refimprove|date=December 2016}} {{self-published|date=December 2016}} }} Many lists exist that provide an overview of large [[software]] [[company|companies]], often called "independent software vendors" ("[[Independent software vendor|ISVs]]"), in the world. The lists differ by [[methodology]] of composition and consequently show substantial differences in both [[Public company|listed companies]] and [[ranking]] of those companies.
== Legend == {| class="wikitable plainrowheads" style="text-align:center;"
|- ! scope="row" | Sales | Annual revenue of company in USD billion in previous fiscal year |- ! scope="row" | FY | Company's current [[fiscal year]] |- ! scope="row" | Market cap | Market capitalization as of February 2017 in USD billion |- ! scope="row" | Headquarters | Location of company's [[headquarters]] |- ! scope="row" | Ref(s). | Reference(s) |}
== Forbes Global 2000 == The [[Forbes Global 2000]] is an annual ranking of the top 2000 [[public companies]] in the world by ''[[Forbes]]'' magazine, based on a mix of four metrics: [[sales]], [[Profit (accounting)|profit]], [[asset]]s and [[market value]]. The Forbes list for software companies includes only [[pure play]] (or nearly pure play) software companies and excludes manufacturers, consumer electronics companies, conglomerates, [[List of IT consulting firms|IT consulting firms]], and computer services companies even if they have large software divisions. For example, [[IBM]] would likely rank #3 in 2017 if its software business unit had been a separate company. The omission of more diversified firms can be useful to investors who are seeking either more or less exposure in the software sector.
The top 10 companies in the 2017 Forbes list for the "Software & Programming" industry are listed in the following table:<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/global2000/list/#industry:Software%20%26%20Programming|title=The World's Biggest Public Companies, Software/Programming|website=Forbes|access-date=2016-05-21}}</ref> {| class="wikitable sortable plainrowheads" style="text-align:center;" |- ! Rank ! colspan=2 |Organization ! Sales (B$) ! FY ! Market cap (B$) ! Headquarters |- | 1 || {{flagicon|United States}} ||[[Microsoft]]|| 85.3 || 2018 || 507.5 || [[Redmond, Washington|Redmond]], WA, US |- | 2 || {{flagicon|United States}} ||[[Alphabet Inc.|Alphabet]]|| 89.9 || 2018 || 579.5 || [[Mountain View, California|Mountain View]], CA, US |- | 3 || {{flagicon|United States}} ||[[IBM]]|| 79.9 || 2018 || 162.4 || [[Armonk, New York|Armonk]], NY, US |- | 4 || {{flagicon|United States}} || [[Oracle Corporation|Oracle]] || 37.4 || 2018 || 182.2 || [[Redwood City, California|Redwood City]], CA, US |- | 5 || {{flagicon|United States}} || [[Facebook]] || 27.6 || 2018 || 407.3 || [[Menlo Park, California|Menlo Park]], CA, US |- | 6 || {{flagicon|China}} || [[Tencent Holdings|Tencent]] || 22.8 || 2018 || 277.1 || [[Shenzhen]], CN |- | 7 || {{flagicon|Germany}} || [[SAP SE|SAP]] || 24.4 || 2018 || 119.7 || [[Walldorf]], DE |- | 8 || {{flagicon|Ireland}} || [[Accenture]] || 35.7 || 2018 || 77.8 || [[Dublin]], IE |- | 9 || {{flagicon|India}} || [[Tata Consultancy Services|TCS]] || 19.08 || 2018 || 102.6 || [[Mumbai]], IN |- | 10 || {{flagicon|China}} || [[Baidu]] || 10.6 || 2018 || 59.9 || [[Beijing]], CN |- |} All values listed in the table are in billion US$, Forbes lists market capitalization as of February 2017.
